WEBVTT

00:13:26.768 --> 00:13:30.276
which progressives use,
actually, really powerfully,

00:13:30.300 --> 00:13:34.529
I think most recently
in gay marriage legalization,

00:13:34.553 --> 00:13:37.519
that actually celebrates
that progress and almost says,

00:13:37.543 --> 00:13:39.768
"Look, there is
an irreversibility to this.

00:13:39.792 --> 00:13:41.204
Get on board the train."

00:13:41.228 --> 00:13:45.129
And maybe we should
find a way of using that more

00:13:45.153 --> 00:13:48.486
in the way that we report progress,
so it doesn't seem complacent.

00:13:48.510 --> 00:13:49.723
It's a challenge to me,

00:13:49.747 --> 00:13:53.410
because people are still fighting
really hard, passionate battles

00:13:53.434 --> 00:13:56.061
and don't want to be told
that your issue doesn't matter

00:13:56.085 --> 00:13:57.982
quite as much as it did 20 years ago.

00:13:58.006 --> 00:13:59.263
SP: Yeah.

00:13:59.287 --> 00:14:04.116
The question of whether
you can identify progress as a thing,